Share with:
General Insurance Placement Broker Job (Manager) (Insurance Brokers), Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Operations
Industry:
Insurance
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
05 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of a local insurance brokerage. Our respected clients is seeking a suitably qualified professional with at least 7 years’ experience in the general insurance industry for the job of General Insurance Placement Broker, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. As a placement broker, you will be responsible to maintain new and existing clients and insurers on the service requirements. The ideal candidate will be someone coming from general insurance industry possessing excellent knowledge of general insurance products and players in the market. The winning candidate will be someone with great analytical and negotiation skills.
Key job responsibilities include:
Maintain new and existing clients and insurers
Ensure satisfying daily delivery service to the clients and insurers
Communicate and negotiate the best package with the insurers according to the clients’ needs
Develop broking plan, quotations and renewal purposes for any business prospects
Prepare any proposal or supporting documents for the prospects
Review and provide recommendation on the current policies and procedures on how to improve the service to both the clients and insurers
Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree in insurance-related major
7 years (min) of experience in general insurance industry
Excellent knowledge of general insurance market and products in Indonesia
Preferably having a degree or certification in insurance (AAAI-K)
Excellent managerial skills
Excellent negotiation and presentation skills
Excellent problem solving skills
Excellent communication skills, both oral and written
Able to work independently and in a team
Fluency in English
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.